    <h1 style="font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: 600; font-size: 40px; line-height: 130%; color: #212121;">Content Report</h1>
    <p style="font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; font-size: 18px; line-height: 150%; color: #212121; margin-bottom: 32px;">VA Directive 6102 requires that VA content be reviewed yearly to ensure information is still relevant. Outdated content will need to be updated or removed to be compliant. <a href="https://va.gov/web">Learn more about VA Directive 6102.</a></p>
    <hr>
    <p style="font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; font-size: 18px; line-height: 150%; color: #212121; margin-top: 32px;">To assist with getting all of your content 6102 compliant within the next year, we will be sending you a monthly report of outdated content, highlighting the most outdated items. To become compliant within a year, you will need to update at least 25 items per month until all items are updated. Your outdated content report will show the top 25 items most overdue at any given time.</p>
    <h2 style="font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: 600; font-size: 24px; line-height: 130%; color: #212121;">Directions</h2>
    <ul style="font-family: sans-serif; font-style: normal; font-weight: 400; font-size: 18px; line-height: 150%; color: #212121;">
      <li>Log in to the Drupal CMS or click “Review” below to go directly to your outdated content. </li>
      <li>Review content for accuracy. Edit or archive if necessary.</li>
      <li>Add the required revision log of what you did. Note what changes were made or if everything was checked and no changes were needed.</li>
      <li>Publish.</li>
    </ul>
